In this article, President Biden expresses his disappointment and frustration with the Supreme Court's decision to strike down his student debt relief program. He highlights the progress his administration has made in expanding Pell Grants, improving the Public Service Loan Forgiveness program, and implementing an Income-Driven Repayment Plan. He also criticizes Republican officials for opposing student debt relief while benefiting from relief programs themselves. Despite the setback, Biden announces a new approach to provide debt relief and a temporary on-ramp repayment program to help borrowers who may struggle to make payments. He assures borrowers that he will continue fighting for student debt relief. The article ends with a brief mention of questions about Afghanistan withdrawal, to which Biden defends his decisions.